Package: dcce
Title: Dynamic Common Correlated Effects Estimation for Panel Data
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R: person("Mustapha", "Wasseja", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "muswaseja@gmail.com")
Description: Estimates heterogeneous coefficient models for large panels
    with cross-sectional dependence. Implements the Mean Group (MG),
    Common Correlated Effects (CCE), and Dynamic CCE (DCCE) estimators
    of Pesaran (2006) and Chudik and Pesaran (2015), the regularized CCE
    of Juodis (2022), the Augmented Mean Group of Eberhardt and Teal
    (2010), and long-run estimators including CS-DL, CS-ARDL, and
    Pooled Mean Group (PMG) (Chudik et al. 2016; Shin et al. 1999).
    Also provides rolling-window estimation, high-dimensional fixed
    effect absorption, spatial CCE via user-supplied weight matrices,
    and structural break tests (Chow and sup-Wald) following Andrews
    (1993), Bai and Perron (1998), and Ditzen, Karavias and Westerlund
    (2024). Supplies a comprehensive cross-sectional dependence test
    suite (Pesaran 2015 CD, Juodis and Reese 2022 CDw, Baltagi et al.
    2012 bias-adjusted CDw+, Fan et al. 2015 PEA, Pesaran and Xie 2021
    CD*), the Pesaran (2007) CIPS panel unit root test, the Westerlund
    (2007) cointegration tests, the Swamy (1970) and Pesaran and
    Yamagata (2008) slope homogeneity tests, a Hausman-type test for
    MG versus pooled, the exponent of cross-sectional dependence from
    Bailey et al. (2016, 2019), information criteria for CSA
    selection, the rank condition classifier, cross-section and wild
    bootstrap inference, and broom-compatible methods.
